    <!-- THE BIG ONE contents-->
    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            ">Munich Security Conference</h2> 
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/munich-security-conference-chairman-speech.png" alt="Munich Security Conference chairman speaks at the conference" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF"> 
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            Munich Security Conference chairman speaks at the conference. Credits: Ina Fassbender/Reuters
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5"><strong>Summary: Global leaders will meet in Munich to discuss the major security challenges, particularly the war in Ukraine.</strong></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">

          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">At the Munich Security Conference, <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-15-02-2025-h1-1-global-leaders-face-pressing-security-challenges?source=website" target="_blank">global leaders face pressing security challenges</a>, mainly the ongoing war in Ukraine. The unity within NATO, which once stood firm against Russia's invasion, shows some cracks. Meanwhile, Europe continues to support Ukraine's resistance and long-term peace through sustained pressure on Russia. Over the next 72 hours, President Trump's team will furnish the details of their plan for Ukraine.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;filter:blur(5px);">President Trump's administration seeks a quicker resolution, even if it means conceding to Russia's demands. Trump's recent shifts include rejecting Ukraine's NATO membership and holding a conversation with Putin, weakening NATO's unity. Critics of this idea say that giving in to Putin means that Putin is enabled to invade other neighboring countries without any repercussions.</p>
        </mj-text> 
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
  </mj-body>
